result.execSummary:
Jesse P Fiedler was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Jesse P Fiedler was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Status conference on December 1, 2022 at 08:30 am.
cc: Def, JCJ, DA, Governor ae 11/2/22

[MK] case called at 2:35pm 
Defendant Jesse P Fiedler in court, in custody.  Public Service Special Prosecutor Melanie Flint appears for the State of Wisconsin. 
Service of the Extradition Complaint is admitted; Mr. Fiedler indicates that he has read and understands the Complaint.  
Extradition rights are reviewed.  Mr. Fiedler indicates that he is waiving his right to counsel. The Court accepts this waiver and finds Mr. Fiedler competent to represent himself. 
Mr. Fiedler agrees that he is the person who the State of Illinois seeks to have extradited, and that he is prepared to waive his extradition rights.
Mr. Fiedler signs four original Waiver of Extradition and Hearing forms in the Court's presence.  
The Court directs that the originals are to be distributed to the Governor's Office, the agent of the demanding state, and the Defendant; one original is to be retained for the court file. 
The Court orders Mr. Fiedler committed to the Jefferson County Jail for a period not to exceed thirty days, awaiting pick-up and transport by Illinois authorities. 
recess 2:42pm. 
[Post hearing: the clerk provides original Waiver of Extradition and Hearing forms to the Defendant and to JESO Sgt. Roberts.] 

NEXT: Status Conference in Branch I (to ensure that Mr. Fiedler has been picked up by Illinois authorities) on December 1st
